LABEL: 0x46
JPN: みんなで食材と機材を、港まで運んで来た。
ENG: We brought all the ingredients and tools we'd gathered to the pier.

LABEL: 0xf2
ENG: "Hey, what do you kids think you're doing?"

LABEL: 0x19c
JPN: 「いいけどよ、役所の許可はあるのか」
ENG: "Not that I care, but did you get permission from the town hall?"

LABEL: 0x266
JPN: 「まぁいいよ。だったら、俺の手伝いってテイでやればいい」
ENG: "Well, whatever. In that case, you can just tell 'em you're helpin' me out, or something."

LABEL: 0x32a
JPN: 「商売敵にそこまでしてくれるのか」
ENG: "You'd really go that far for your competition?"

LABEL: 0x396
JPN: 「これからずっとってわけじゃないんだろう」
ENG: "Not like you're plannin' to stick around forever or anything, are you?"

LABEL: 0x430
ENG: "Now lessee. This what you're looking to sell?"

LABEL: 0x59a
JPN: 準備が整い、調理していく。
ENG: We finished setting up the stall and started cooking.

LABEL: 0x5c4
JPN: 港に漂う香ばしい匂いと、目新しい屋台ののぼりは、自然と人目を引き始めた。
ENG: The fragrance of the food combined with the novelty of a fresh new stall naturally drew quite a bit of attention.

LABEL: 0x6ba
JPN: 情報は瞬く間に狭い島に広がったらしい。
ENG: The news about us spread like wildfire through the island, it would seem.

LABEL: 0x6f0
JPN: 昼を過ぎた辺りから、次々と人が訪れるようになった。
ENG: Starting at a bit past noon people just kept coming and coming.

LABEL: 0x732
JPN: この島にこんなに人がいたのかと、意外なくらいだ。
ENG: More people stopped by than I thought lived on the island, period.

LABEL: 0x772
JPN: 島民のほとんどが来ているんじゃないか？
ENG: It felt like the majority of the island's population paid us a visit.

LABEL: 0xa68
JPN: 珍しがって集まっていた人の姿も、ほぼ途切れたらしい。
ENG: The crowd of curious onlookers had mostly dispersed.

LABEL: 0xaac
JPN: 材料はまだ残っているけど、そろそろ店じまいするしかないだろう。
ENG: We still had some ingredients left over, but I figured it was time for us to close up.

LABEL: 0xb98
ENG: "How much did we make in the end?"

LABEL: 0xce0
JPN: 見物人は多かったが、見てるだけであまり買ってくれなかったんだよな。
ENG: A ton of people stopped by, but most of them just watched instead of buying something.

LABEL: 0xd68
JPN: 「ま、まぁ健闘したということで」
ENG: "W-Well, let's just call it a good effort."

LABEL: 0xdd8
JPN: 「徳田も、きっとがんばりを認めてくれるだろう」
ENG: "I'm sure Tokuda will recognize our efforts too."

LABEL: 0xf3c
ENG: "Not as much as we were aiming for, but..."

LABEL: 0x100c
ENG: "We'll just have to leave the rest to our bargaining skills."

LABEL: 0x11b2
JPN: 「まさか一日で目標を達成するとは」
ENG: "To think we'd reach our goal in just a single day!"

LABEL: 0x11ee
JPN: しろはの手には、報酬が入った封筒。
ENG: Shiroha held the fruits of our labor in an envelope.

LABEL: 0x1338
JPN: 「結局俺自身はなにもできなかった」
ENG: "In the end, I didn't help at all, myself."

LABEL: 0x1382
JPN: 「ほとんどしろはがやったことだ」

LABEL: 0x13ca
JPN: 「この金は、しろはが受け取るべきだ」

LABEL: 0x1448
JPN: 「しろはが気にしている癖毛を直すのに使えばいい」
ENG: "You should use it to go fix up that frizzy hair you're always so worried about."

LABEL: 0x14d2
JPN: 「いつ癖毛を気にしていることになっていたっ」
ENG: "Since when have I been worried about having frizzy hair?"

LABEL: 0x1528
JPN: 「してなかったか？　俺の記憶違いか……。気にしてたのは、俺の従姉妹だったか……」
ENG: "You aren't? Did I misremember...? Was it my cousin who was worried about that...?"

LABEL: 0x1590
ENG: "Whatever, just go buy the table already."

LABEL: 0x15c2
JPN: 「今更、いらないと言われても、しろはだって困るだろう」
ENG: "Changing your mind at the last minute's just gonna put Shiroha on the spot."

LABEL: 0x17b8
ENG: "And how exactly did you get this money?"

LABEL: 0x17ea
JPN: 「うちは出所の怪しい金には関わらないぞ」
ENG: "We don't take dirty money here, you know?"

LABEL: 0x1872
ENG: "This is the fruit of our combined strength!"

LABEL: 0x18ea
ENG: "Hmph. You people reek of foul play."

LABEL: 0x192e
JPN: 「正確にはほとんどしろはの手柄だが」
ENG: "Technically it's pretty much all thanks to Shiroha, actually."

LABEL: 0x19cc
JPN: 「主にあいつが、いろいろとがんばった結果だ」
ENG: "Her hard work's what really got us this far."

LABEL: 0x1a94
ENG: "Hey, that isn't what we agreed on!"

LABEL: 0x1ac0
ENG: "Just shut up and take the table already."

LABEL: 0x1ba6
ENG: "Do you have a thing for Shiroha?"

LABEL: 0x1c04
ENG: "Then... do you have a thing for me?"

LABEL: 0x1c64
ENG: "Then who do you have a thing for?"

LABEL: 0x1d04
ENG: "Like I said, why would you even say that!?"

LABEL: 0x1d32
ENG: "It's not a matter of having a thing for anyone!"

LABEL: 0x1d62
JPN: 「うちがこの島で商いが出来るのも、鳴瀬家のおかげだ」
ENG: "We owe our business on this island to the Naruse family."

LABEL: 0x1dda
JPN: 「知らん。が、とにかくそういうことらしい」
ENG: "Hell if I know. But that's what they tell me, in any case."

LABEL: 0x1e1c
JPN: 「鳴瀬から金を取ったと知れたら、親父に俺が殴られる」
ENG: "My old man would smack me into next week if he found out I accepted money from a Naruse."

LABEL: 0x1e68
JPN: 「卓球台はあそこだ、持って行ってくれ」
ENG: "The ping-pong table's over there. Just take it, please."

LABEL: 0x1eca
JPN: 「しかしまさか、４万円も用意してくるとは」
ENG: "Still, to think you got ahold of forty thousand yen in such a short period!"

LABEL: 0x1f0c
JPN: 「やるじゃないか。見直したぞ」
ENG: "Not bad! I'm seeing you in a new light."

LABEL: 0x1f90
JPN: 後ろめたいので、封筒を差し出して見せる。
ENG: My conscience got the better of me. I handed him the envelope so he could take a look.

LABEL: 0x20f8
JPN: 押しつけるように渡された卓球台。
ENG: We stood beside the ping-pong table that Tokuda more or less foisted on us.

LABEL: 0x2128
JPN: 「これを山の小屋まで運ぶのか」
ENG: "Are we supposed to carry this thing all the way up the mountain?"

LABEL: 0x21c2
JPN: 「台車でもあればいいんだが」
ENG: "It'd be nice if we had a trolley or something."

LABEL: 0x221c
JPN: 「この大きさは、乗らないだろう」
ENG: "That might not even be enough, just look at this thing."

LABEL: 0x2254
JPN: 「誰かに軽トラ出してもらえないのか。倉庫があるなら車道も通ってるだろ」
ENG: "Could we get someone to drive it up in a mini truck? If there's a shed up there, there must be some kind of road, right?"

LABEL: 0x22cc
JPN: 「昔はな。土砂崩れがあって、そのまま放置されてる」
ENG: "Used to be, yeah. But then we had a couple landslides, and they never bothered to fix it."

LABEL: 0x2316
JPN: 「もとの卓球台はどうやって運んだんだ」
ENG: "How'd you get the old table up there?"

LABEL: 0x23a8
JPN: 「じゃあ持って行くしかないのか」
ENG: "Guess we're gonna have to carry it."

LABEL: 0x24f6
JPN: 「こらこら。女の子に何させてるの」
ENG: "Hey, hey, what in the world are you making a girl do?"

LABEL: 0x26cc
JPN: 「なんで私まで……こんなことを」
ENG: "How did I... get dragged into this?"

LABEL: 0x2714
JPN: 「特訓だと思えば、都合がいいだろう」
ENG: "Just think of it as training! Two birds with one stone, right?"

LABEL: 0x2760
ENG: "You're the only one who'd ever feel that way!"

LABEL: 0x2896
JPN: 無事、やたらと立派な卓球台が掘っ立て小屋の中に設置された。
ENG: We successfully installed the extravagant ping-pong table in the middle of the shed.

LABEL: 0x28e0
ENG: It looked pretty out of place.

LABEL: 0x2978
JPN: 卓球台を前に、感無量といった感じだ。
ENG: He stood in front of the table, seemingly overwhelmed with emotion.

LABEL: 0x2b2a
JPN: 「ええ。しょっちゅう泊まってるんだが」
ENG: "C'mon, I sleep here all the time."

LABEL: 0x2c00
JPN: 「でもあたしも、すぐに山降りるのは無理そう。疲れた」
ENG: "I don't think I can make it back down the mountain any time soon, either. I'm beat."

LABEL: 0x2d8e
JPN: 一休みしてだべっているうちに、外はあっという間に真っ暗になっていた。
ENG: We chatted away as we took a break together, and before we knew it it was pitch black outside.

LABEL: 0x2de2
JPN: 俺達は誰も帰らず、そのまま倉庫で、ぼんやりしていた。
ENG: We sat around in the shed. Nobody seemed interested in heading home.

LABEL: 0x2e40
JPN: 山の上から見るせいか、いっそう近く見える。
ENG: They seemed a bit closer than normal, maybe since we were on a mountain.

LABEL: 0x2e8a
JPN: 「改めて気にすることもなかったが……こうして見ると、すごいな」
ENG: "Been a while since I really noticed 'em, but the stars sure are something from up here, huh?"

LABEL: 0x2ee0
JPN: 「これで観光客呼んだら、金がとれるぞ」
ENG: "I bet you could make a killing charging tourists to come up here."

LABEL: 0x2f30
JPN: 「卓球台がたくさん買えるな」
ENG: "Enough to buy a ton of ping-pong tables."

LABEL: 0x3078
JPN: 「そういえば、稼いだ金だけどさ」
ENG: "Speaking of which, about the money we made..."

LABEL: 0x30b2
JPN: 卓球台を譲られたので、代金は丸々手元に残った。
ENG: Since we got the table for free in the end, all the money we'd made was still left over.

LABEL: 0x30f0
JPN: 「しろはが受け取るのがいいと思うんだけどどうだろ？」
ENG: "I think Shiroha should take it. How 'bout you guys?"

LABEL: 0x313e
JPN: 実質稼いだのはしろはで、卓球台を譲られた理由もしろはにあるらしい。
ENG: Not only was Shiroha the driving force behind our earnings, she was also the reason we got the ping-pong table for free.

LABEL: 0x3214
ENG: "No, this time you really should take it."

LABEL: 0x32be
ENG: "I don't know what I'd do with all this."

LABEL: 0x3330
ENG: "Like, in the stock market, or something?"

LABEL: 0x339c
ENG: "I... really don't have any use for it, after all."

LABEL: 0x33f8
JPN: 「確かしろはは、癖毛が気になってるんだっけ」
ENG: "If I remember correctly, weren't you worried about your frizzy hair?"

LABEL: 0x34be
JPN: 「天善君が言ってたけど、否定したでしょ。おぼろげに記憶しないでほしいっ」
ENG: "Tenzen-kun said it, but I denied it, didn't I? Please stop making assumptions based on things you barely remember."

LABEL: 0x3580
JPN: 「スイカバーをたらふく食べるとか」
ENG: "You could buy a truckload of watermelon bars?"

LABEL: 0x3728
JPN: 「分かった。じゃあ残りは、少年団の会費に組みこむとしよう」
ENG: "Got it. I'll add the rest to the Youth Association's budget."

LABEL: 0x37a0
JPN: 「なんてつまらない使い方だ」
ENG: "What a boring way to spend money."

LABEL: 0x3868
ENG: "But still, what should I do with this?"

LABEL: 0x38c4
JPN: 「この島じゃ使うような場所ないしね」
ENG: "There really isn't anywhere to spend money on this island."

LABEL: 0x390e
JPN: 「船に乗って、本土まで行ってきたら？」
ENG: "Why not take the ferry to the mainland?"

LABEL: 0x395a
JPN: 「行けば何か欲しいもの見つかるかもしれないわよ」
ENG: "You might find something you want over there."

LABEL: 0x39e2
JPN: 「でもあまり、１人で行ったことないから」
ENG: "But I've never really gone alone, so..."

LABEL: 0x3a50
JPN: 「鷹原が付き合ったらどうだ」
ENG: "Then why not take Takahara with you?"

LABEL: 0x3cf0
JPN: そそくさと去って行った。
ENG: She left. In an awful hurry, too.

LABEL: 0x3d4a
ENG: "Maybe I should've kept my mouth shut."

LABEL: 0x3de4
ENG: I made my way back home.

LABEL: 0x3e28
JPN: 「そんなことがあったんですよ」

LABEL: 0x3eaa
JPN: 「卓球台なら、蔵にあったのに」
ENG: "We had a ping-pong table in this shed the entire time, though!"

LABEL: 0x3f04
JPN: 「おばーちゃんの遺品って、どうなってるんですか」
ENG: "What on earth is wrong with this estate?"

LABEL: 0x3f4e
JPN: 「別に、廃品回収を営んでいたわけじゃないですよね」
ENG: "She wasn't running some kind of waste disposal service or anything, right?"

LABEL: 0x3faa
JPN: 「あはは。多趣味な人だったから」
ENG: "Ahaha. She was a woman of many interests."

LABEL: 0x40f4
JPN: あ、うみちゃんが呼んでいる。

LABEL: 0x41ea
JPN: うみちゃんは、軽く肩をすくめた。

LABEL: 0x42e6
JPN: 『わたくし、鳴瀬しろはと申します』

LABEL: 0x4348
JPN: 聞き慣れない口調に戸惑う。なるせしろはともうします。
ENG: Her tone was so formal I got confused for a second. My name is...? My name is Naruse Shiroha...?

LABEL: 0x452a
JPN: 「……なんでそんなに硬い口調なんだ」

LABEL: 0x4568
JPN: 電話で緊張しているんだろうけど。
ENG: I figured talking on the phone made her nervous.

LABEL: 0x4620
ENG: "Would you happen to be free tomorrow?"

LABEL: 0x4652
JPN: 「俺はいつでもぶらぶらしてるだけだよ」
ENG: "I'm always free. So free I could die of freedom."

LABEL: 0x4728
JPN: 『ごちそうさせていただきます』

LABEL: 0x4910
ENG: "Please allow me to pay for you!"

LABEL: 0x4988
ENG: "Should we meet up at the diner, then?"

LABEL: 0x49c6
ENG: "At the harbor, if you don't mind!"

LABEL: 0x4a26
JPN: 『しからば、何卒よろしくお願いしまする』
ENG: "Being in that case, please give me your kindest regards thank you kindly!"

LABEL: 0x4a86
JPN: ……最後の方、どんどん敬語が崩壊していてドキドキした。
ENG: ...That last part was an absolute mess of hyper-polite nonsense.

LABEL: 0x4baa
JPN: 「港でおごってもらうことになりましたです」
ENG: "It has become apparent that I am to be treated at the harbor tomorrow."
